                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1165">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Notice issued to the press</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The State Department has from time to time received information directly or
                    indirectly to the effect that belligerent nations had arranged with banks in the
                    United States for credits in various sums. While loans to belligerents have been
                    disapproved, this Government has not felt that it was justified in interposing
                    objection to the credit arrangements which have been brought to its attention.
                    It has neither approved these nor disapproved—it has simply taken no action in
                    the premises and expressed no opinion.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
